1.title: Chris & Nora vs. Lisa & Danny
1.plot: It's the battle of the condominiums as Chris and Nora have a slow reno start and are unlucky in fundraising while Lisa and Danny strike the community jackpot but are delayed in their important bathroom project.

2.title: Suzanne & Kevin vs. Dan & Sheri
2.plot: Suzanne and Kevin must fix two years' worth of unfinished projects in just two weeks while Dan and Sheri, despite help from a lot of friends, find themselves in a race against time to complete all of their renos. It's anyone's game.

3.title: Jeff & Joanne vs. Jill & Joel
3.plot: Jeff and Joanne tackle their kitchen reno with gusto resulting in a risky expense tally. Joel and Jill keep their expenses low but jeopardize their chances of finishing on time with their slow pace.

4.title: Trevor & Bonnie vs. Natalie & Ray
4.plot: When Trevor and Bonnie face a power outage and a trip to emergency, it's up to their large team to conquer their reno delays. Natalie and Ray have a huge task ahead of them but fail to assemble a team to help. Can they do it alone?

5.title: Pat & Sue vs. Tracey & Angie
5.plot: This race is down to the wire as Pat and Sue's tight budget forces them to agonize over every penny spent while Tracey and Angie rely on their huge contingent of helpers to deal with all of their unexpected issues.

6.title: Lisa & Christie vs. Andrew & Michelle
6.plot: Things really heat up for Lisa when she loses Christie and struggles to complete projects without her reno partner while Andrew and Michelle struggle to complete their renovation nightmare.

7.title: Lynne & Dave vs. Kyle & Carol
7.plot: Tired right out of the gate, Lynne updates and de-clutters her small starter home with fiancé, Dave while Kyle and Carol take on a time sucking basement reno to increase their home's value. Who will make it to the finish line?

8.title: Suzanne & Kat vs. Guy & Kelly
8.plot: With little money in the bank, Suzanne and Kat must fundraise enough to front their reno expenses while Kelly and Guy struggle with an exhausting list of projects, despite raising a surplus of funds.

9.title: AJ & Ashley vs. Mitch & Laura
9.plot: AJ and Ashley attempt to repair two years' worth of smelly pet damage to their home while their competition Mitch, with new girlfriend Laura, faces the past as he de-clutters and updates the home his father left to him.

10.title: Nicki & Tori vs. Angela & Dave
10.plot: Nicki and Tori transform their home from frat-house style to mainstream appeal with lots of help from their dad as Angela and Dave strive to maximize their home's appeal with high-end fixtures in this battle of the 'burbs.

11.title: Brigitte & Dave vs. Peter & Shelagh
11.plot: Brigitte and Dave tackle an enormous job list in the hopes of getting their massive house market ready while Peter and Shelagh prioritize their workload and tackle fewer projects. Which strategy will be the key to the prize?

12.title: Lucille & Natalie vs. Paula & Josh
12.plot: It's a mother-daughter, mother-son rivalry. Lucille and Natalie attempt to complete their suburban-home update with high style while Paula and Josh tackle a complete design overhaul of their small city house.

13.title: Chris & Cherry vs. Matthew & Michelle
13.plot: To overcome their lack of DIY skills, Chris and Cherry rely on their friends to do the heavy lifting while Matthew and Michelle decide that their faith is more important than their renos.

14.title: Trisha & Alec vs. Betts & Samantha
14.plot: Trisha and Alec get ahead quickly with a strong start, while Betts and Samantha are slow out of the gate. But will the tortoise be able to overtake the hare in this rivalry between Mother-Son and Mother-Daughter teams?

15.title: Lia vs. Vladimir
15.plot: Lia attempts to squeeze more square footage out of her tiny starter home with some key renovations while Vladimir is completely overwhelmed with the massive amount of work needed to be done in his large home.

16.title: Alison & Leo vs. Chantale & Fred
16.plot: Alison and Leo are anxious to sell their poorly maintained, century old house and find a suitable home for their family of five. They jump into action demolishing the kitchen and bathroom, but when Penny's design plans force them to rip up seven layers of flooring they start to wonder if their efforts could have been better spent elsewhere. As Alison and Leo both put in time at their day jobs, they rely on friends to keep things rolling. Alison holds a bake and toy sale to raise funds, but it's her impressive barter for cabinetry that keeps costs low. In order to ...

17.title: Chris & Sheryl vs. Al & Valerie
17.plot: It's a photo finish for these two homes with huge potential. Sheryl and Chris' kitchen gets a major transformation for a minor amount of cash, while Al and Valerie's basement make-over on a zero dollar budget keeps the race close.

18.title: Jimmy vs. Iain
18.plot: While Jimmy is in the midst of renovating his bachelor's pad to unload it, he has a major surprise for his girlfriend Lisa. Iain must sell his design-challenged house in order to reunite his family in another city.

19.title: Gwen & Aldo vs. Sue
19.plot: It's a head to head battle as both sets of homeowners work to bring yesterday's style into today! Gwen and Aldo chose their home to raise their young family, but now that their daughters are grown up and Gwen's new home-based business is about to take off, they need to find a more accommodating space. Their jam-packed suburban home shows really small and the forest green carpets and floral couches beg for a re-do. Aldo puts his handyman skills to the test and takes on an entire kitchen overhaul with the help of friends and family, while Gwen gets picked on for her ...

20.title: Scott & Dawn vs. Joel and Mary Ann
20.plot: It's the battle of the bungalows. With both teams desperate to upsize, they tackle similar projects to increase curb appeal and maximize square footage. But there can only be one winner of Paul's commission-free listing.

21.title: Jason & Tara vs. Eric and Shannon
21.plot: Jason and Tara need to take their tired townhome from the 80s into the now, while Eric and Shannon have to complete a house full of half-finished projects. Both homes need serious help if they're going to attract buyers.

22.title: Lynn vs. John
22.plot: Lynn tackles a major basement facelift with the help of her son and brother while John barters his way through an update of the entire main floor in this battle between two rural homes.

23.title: Don & Donna vs. Lisa & René
23.plot: In the tightest reno race to date, this small town showdown sees huge community support for both teams as Don and Donna update their little bungalow and Lisa and René transform their turn of the century home.

24.title: Lori vs. Christine
24.plot: Christine and Lori face off in this battle of the single moms. Christine is tasked with a major kitchen update in her tiny home, while Lori has to transform the main bathroom in her huge house to woo buyers. May the best mom win.

25.title: Alex & Mark vs. Daniel & Felicity
25.plot: It's a rural edition of the All For Nothing? renovation rivalry. Alex and Mark update their country home situated in the middle of a corn field while Daniel and Felicity give their cabin in the woods main stream appeal.

26.title: Randy & Sarita vs. Jean-Marcel & Melodie
26.plot: Jean-Marcel and Melodie make remarkable headway in the first days of demolition whereas Randy and Sarita don't even know where to start. Paul and Penny are disappointed in both teams at the half way check-in. Will they pull it together?

1.title: Big Family vs. Big Family
1.plot: Two large families by today's standards, the Hermans and the Awadas adopt completely different strategies to completing their home renos. The Awadas take a slow and steady approach to realizing their design plans, resisting some of Paul and Penny's advice along the way. The Herman's start strong with lots of help, strictly following the design plans - and then some! As the two weeks quickly come to a close, the Awadas manage to finally recruit some much needed help and the Herman's receive a tough blow - their deal for free staging furniture falls through. In the end,...

2.title: City House vs. Country House
2.plot: Darlene starts strong by scoring a barter deal for new siding. She and Chris jump right in helping to remove the old siding to speed up the job.They quickly start to question the rest of Penny's design plan and how much can be accomplished in just two weeks. Resistant to any more constructive criticism, Darlene refuses to let Paul and Penny into her home during their check-in. Al and Jen manage to sell a big ticket item to bank roll their projects. With Al still recovering from a serious illness, they work hard to recruit family and friends to help with the heavy ...

3.title: Upsizers vs. Downsizers
3.plot: Empty nesters Chris and Henry let their money do the heavy lifting when it comes to the renos while Aaren and Brianne invest sweat equity into their young family's cramped and cluttered home.

4.title: Family Life vs. Single Life
4.plot: Cory and Jen Besharah juggle work and two young sons with reno projects at their family home in a subdivision outside the city while housemates Terri and Heidi upgrade their urban singles' townhome after three years of neglect.

5.title: Bartering vs. Bargaining
5.plot: Dayna puts her bartering skills to the test to keep her reno costs low while Chris and Kitty bargain their way through the competition. Who will prevail in the bartering versus bargaining rivalry?

6.title: Growing Family vs. Growing Family
6.plot: The Kangs and the Muis both have small starter homes that can no longer accommodate their growing families. They will battle to save big dollars in this competition to finance larger homes. Who will come out on top?

7.title: Modern vs. Unique
7.plot: Mat and Sonja make improvements to their modern chic city home while Vicki works to increase the value of her unique small-town home that used to be a church. It's a fight to the finish between Modern and Unique.

8.title: Starter Home vs. Semi-Detached
8.plot: Paula and Rob focus their efforts on fundraising while Jacob and Shoba sink a lot of time and energy into a Penny design feature that Paul doesn't support. It's a mad scramble to the finish in this Starter Home vs. Semi-Detached battle.

9.title: De-Clutter vs. Construction
9.plot: Chantal and Phil's small city home is overwhelmed with stuff and needs to show much larger. Martina attempts to elevate the value of her outdated rural home. Who will prevail in the clutter versus construction competition?

10.title: Suburb vs. City
10.plot: Roxy and Jeff Gregoire update their cluttered suburban home while Kathleen McGovern takes her city home to the next level. It all comes down to a battle of wills to finish on time.

11.title: Mother & Daughter vs. Husband & Wife
11.plot: Denise and Melanie Reid recruit an army of family and friends to help with their renos while Jeff and Jill Alexander barter for assistance with their home improvements. Which will make for the winning strategy?

12.title: Small Town vs. Small Town
12.plot: Homeowners Jonathan and Emilie take on Dan and Stacey in a small town rivalry. Both teams are struck by illness causing much delay; will either team finish their renos on time?

13.title: Chaos vs. Calm
13.plot: Suzanne and Costa's 'go big or go home' approach results in a chaotic two weeks, while Robin and Steve's methodical reno is very calm and orderly. With these radically different approaches, which method is the one to get the win?

imdb.plot outline: All For Nothing? is one part design transformation series, and one part fast-paced real estate drama that pits homeowner against homeowner in a competition to ready their neglected homes for sale. The catch? They have to attempt to do it all for nothing. Motivation is high, as the two sets of homeowners compete for a money-saving prize: the commission-free listing services from Ottawa's top real estate agent and one of the shows hosts, Paul Rushforth. Jam-packed full of ideas and tips from our top notch designer, Penny Southam, and solid real estate advice from real estate host, each episode inspires budget strapped viewers to take on the challenge of achieving professional pre-listing make-overs. The question is, can they do it... All For Nothing?
